AGI Donald Trump's America? "For the moment, it cannot be ignored that many of Trump's first interventions have brought some immediate advantage to the United States, but in the long run his strategy to put the other countries continuously under pressure will turn into an increasingly violent centrifugal force, capable of separating and dividing the Western community." To say it is Marina Berlusconi in the anticipations of the interview, published on the Sheet of tomorrow, to the director, Claudio Cerasa.
&nbsp;
The president of Fininvest and the Mondadori group adds: "I really hope that the country that has always been the main Western guarantor does not now have a president who wants to become the 'hijacker' of the West itself, thus demolishing everything that America has been in the last eighty years." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Marina Berlusconi also says about Ukraine: "To put an end to this terrible conflict, a compromise will be inevitable, > but I am absolutely convinced that the end of the war should not coincide with the Kiev surrender and the victory of Moscow. Ukraine has the necessary guarantees for its security and independence. If it were a peace on the skin of Kiev and Europe, I don't think it could be considered a good thing. If Europe is cut off from the solution that seems to be proving it will also have to make a serious self-critical." &nbsp;>

